// BT-2207: E2E fixture for `SystemNavigation unusedSelectors`.
//
// `UnusedRuntimeCalled` overrides `hash` — a runtime-called selector (invoked by
// hashed collections, not via a source-visible send). Crucially, `hash` is NOT
// sent anywhere in stdlib source, so the sent-set does NOT cover it: the ONLY
// thing keeping this override out of the unused report is the
// `runtimeCalledSelectors` exclusion. The body is real Beamtalk (not
// `@primitive` / `@intrinsic`), so the primitive heuristic does not cover it
// either — making this a genuine test of the runtime-called-override exclusion
// (unlike, say, `printString`, which stdlib also sends directly and which the
// sent-set would exclude regardless).

Object subclass: UnusedRuntimeCalled

  // Runtime-called override with a real (non-primitive) body: reached through
  // hashed-collection machinery, never a source-visible Beamtalk send.
  hash -> Integer => 42
